# Documentation Convention

The `docs/` directory is the canonical location for all durable design documents, feature specs, and plans.

- When designing a new feature or system, write the design doc to `docs/<name>.md`
- When implementation changes make an existing design doc outdated, update it to reflect the current state
- Use Cursor's CreatePlan tool only for ephemeral in-session task tracking, not for persistent documentation

## Existing docs

- `docs/game-design.md` — Full architecture and system design
- `docs/ai-system-design.md` — AI opponent architecture
- `docs/visual-effects-design.md` — Particle and effects system
- `docs/implementation-plan.md` — Gameplay spec and evolution roadmap
